  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6602.61 sitting just below the massive +27.7B gamma wall at 6605, dealers are positioned to aggressively sell any push higher into that resistance level while simultaneously defending the -14.9B negative gamma support at 6590. The PIN regime confirms dealers are long gamma and will provide stabilizing flows, but the 79.1% 1-minute GEX surge indicates rapidly shifting positioning that could create temporary volatility spikes before mean reversion kicks in. Key inflection points are clear: 6590 downside support where dealer buying accelerates, 6605 immediate resistance where dealer selling intensifies, and 6612 GEX flip level that would shift the entire hedging dynamic if breached.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect price to get pinned between 6590-6605 with dealers capping moves in both directions.",
